  "prompt": "Do clairvoyant readings work?",
  "response": "The effectiveness of clairvoyant readings largely depends on individual beliefs and experiences. Some people report feeling a strong sense of clarity, guidance, or comfort from such readings, while others remain skeptical. Scientifically, there is no empirical evidence to support the claims made by clairvoyants. Many skeptics argue that any accuracy in readings can be attributed to psychological phenomena, such as the Barnum effect, where vague statements are interpreted as personally meaningful.\n\nUltimately, whether clairvoyant readings \"work\" can be subjective and varies from person to person. If someone finds value in the experience, then it can be seen as beneficial for them, regardless of the underlying mechanisms.",
